article.headline: CS Northridge 64, S. Dakota St. 63
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Thomas Shewmake's two free throws with 21 seconds left proved to be the difference as Cal State Northridge defeated South Dakota State 64-63 Tuesday night at Frost Arena. Calvin Chitwood came off the bench to lead the Matadors (13-14) with 18 points. He was 7-for-11 from the floor. Shewmake scored 13 points and collected 12 of his team's 37 rebounds. For South Dakota State (5-22), Kai Williams and Jose Frias each scored a game-high 19 points. Michael Loney led the Jackrabbits with eight rebounds. The Matadors led the entire first half and were up 32-28 at halftime. A Garrett Callahan jump shot gave the Jacks their first lead, 39-38, with 13:21 left. SDSU went on a 5-0 run and had its largest lead at 50-45 with 9:16 remaining. Northridge regained the lead with just less than 6 minutes left and held on until the final minute, when a basket by Frias and a free throw gave South Dakota State a 63-62 lead. Shewmake then was fouled in the post and made both free throws. The Jacks got the ball to Frias, whose short jumper rimmed out in the final seconds.
